  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Critical food and Nutrition assistance to Burundian Refugees (WFP PRRO 200744: Food and Nutrition Assistance to Refugees and Returnees)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CERF funds will support WFP&apos;s monthly dry rations through general food distribution to some 30,000 refugees at Bugesera and Nyanza reception centers and Mahama refugee camp over a four-month period.  In addition, funds will support the procurement of supplementary feeding commodities and High Energy Biscuits to complement the dry rations and to treat moderately acute malnourished children.  In total, some 1,900 metric tons of food commodities will be procured and distributed in four months starting from May to August 2015.</narrative>
  </description>
